org.batfish.datamodel.table

Class Row

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.batfish.datamodel.table.Row
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Row>

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class Row
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Row>
    Represents one row of the table answer. Each row is basically a map of key value pairs, where the key is the column name and the value (currently) is JsonNode.

      • of

        public static Row of(java.lang.Object... objects)
        Returns a new Row with the given entries.

        objects should be an even number of parameters, where the 0th and every even parameter is a String representing the name of a column.

      • of

        public static Row of(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,ColumnMetadata> columns,
                     java.lang.Object... objects)
        Returns a new Row with the given entries.

        objects should be an even number of parameters, where the 0th and every even parameter is a String representing the name of a column. The columns names and the actual objects (in odd parameters) must be compliant with the metadata map in columns.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Row o)
        Compares two Rows. The current implementation ignores primary keys of the table and compares everything, mainly to provide consistent ordering of answers. This will need to change when we start using the primary keys for something.
